# Medication Administration Dashboard - Project Requirements

## Project Overview

The Medication Administration Dashboard is a web-based patient medication tracking system designed for nurses and healthcare staff. The dashboard will allow users to monitor scheduled medications, record medication administration, and review medication history for a patient during a selected time period.

The system should provide a simple, responsive, and secure interface for managing medication schedules and administration records.

## Primary Goals

1. Display patient medication schedules by time window.
2. Allow nurses to record medication administration using initials.
3. Provide monthly medication tracking visibility.
4. Protect sensitive patient information.
5. Maintain a clean and easy-to-use dashboard interface.

## System Type

* Web-based application
* Responsive design for desktop and tablet use
* Single patient dashboard initially
* Expandable for multiple patients in future versions

## Patient Header Section

The top section of the dashboard will display patient information.

Visible Information:

* Patient Name
* Patient ID
* Room Number
* Medication Alerts
* Allergies

Sensitive Information:

* Date of Birth (DOB)
* Medical Record Number (MRN)
* Diagnosis
* Emergency Contact Information

Sensitive fields should remain hidden by default and only reveal when:

* User hovers over the field
  OR
* User clicks a "Reveal Information" button

Security Note:
Hover-only interactions should have mobile/tablet alternatives.

## Time Filter Options

The top header must include time-based filtering options.

Required Filters:

1. AM
2. PM
3. Custom Time Range

AM Filter:

* Displays all medications scheduled during morning hours.

PM Filter:

* Displays all medications scheduled during evening/night hours.

Custom Time Range:

* Allows users to select:

  * Start Time
  * End Time
* Dashboard updates dynamically to show medications scheduled within the selected period.

## Medication Schedule Display

The dashboard should display medications in a monthly schedule format.

Layout Requirements:

* Current month displayed by default
* Dates displayed as rows
* Medications displayed as columns
* Each medication/date intersection contains an empty clickable box

Example Layout:

| Date | Aspirin | Insulin | Metformin |
| ---- | ------- | ------- | --------- |
| 1    | [ ]     | [ ]     | [ ]       |
| 2    | [ ]     | [ ]     | [ ]       |

Medication Information:
Each medication should include:

* Medication Name
* Dosage
* Administration Route
* Scheduled Time
* Frequency
* Start Date
* End Date
* Special Instructions

## Medication Administration Entry

Nurses should be able to click an empty medication box to record administration.

When clicked:

* User may:

  * Enter initials
  * Select status
  * Add optional notes

Medication Status Options:

* Administered
* Missed
* Refused
* Held
* Late

System should automatically record:

* Timestamp
* User/Nurse ID
* Date of action

## Color Coding

Recommended status colors:

* Green = Administered
* Yellow = Pending
* Red = Missed
* Gray = Held

Color coding should improve quick visual recognition.

## Update / Save Functionality

A persistent "Update" or "Save Changes" button should appear at the bottom of the dashboard.

Requirements:

* Save all modifications
* Confirm successful update
* Prevent accidental data loss
* Optional auto-save functionality

Optional Features:

* Undo changes
* Save draft
* Change history tracking

## Authentication & User Roles

The system should support secure user authentication.

User Types:

* Nurse
* Administrator
* Doctor

Requirements:

* Username/password login
* Session management
* Role-based permissions

Examples:

* Nurses can update medication records
* Administrators can edit schedules
* Doctors can review records

## Audit Trail

The system should maintain an audit log for all actions.

Audit Information:

* User name
* Action performed
* Timestamp
* Previous value
* Updated value

Example:
"Nurse AB marked Aspirin as administered at 8:02 AM."

## Database & Data Storage

The system must support persistent storage.

Recommended Storage:

* SQLite (prototype)
  OR
* PostgreSQL/MySQL (production)

Stored Data:

* Patient information
* Medication schedules
* Medication administration records
* User accounts
* Audit logs

## Technical Requirements

Frontend:

* HTML5
* CSS3
* JavaScript

Recommended Frameworks:

* Tailwind CSS
* Bootstrap
  OR
* React (optional future enhancement)

Backend (Optional Future Phase):

* Node.js + Express
  OR
* Python Flask/Django

Database:

* SQLite for development
* PostgreSQL for production

## Responsive Design

The dashboard should function on:

* Desktop computers
* Tablets
* Mobile devices

Requirements:

* Touch-friendly controls
* Readable font sizes
* Responsive table layouts

## Accessibility Requirements

The system should support accessibility standards.

Requirements:

* Keyboard navigation
* High contrast support
* Screen reader compatibility
* Large clickable elements

## Future Enhancements

Possible future features include:

* Multiple patient support
* Medication reminders
* Email/SMS alerts
* PDF export
* Printable medication sheets
* Search and filtering
* Dark mode
* Analytics dashboard
* Barcode medication scanning

## Security Requirements

Because patient information is sensitive, the system should include:

* Encrypted connections (HTTPS)
* Secure authentication
* Protected patient information
* Audit logging
* Role-based access control

Compliance considerations:

* HIPAA compliance (United States)

## Recommended Development Phases

Phase 1:

* Static HTML dashboard
* Medication schedule display
* Basic interaction

Phase 2:

* Save/update functionality
* Local database integration

Phase 3:

* Authentication system
* Audit logging
* Role permissions

Phase 4:

* Responsive/mobile optimization
* Advanced reporting
* Production deployment

## Final Deliverable

The completed system should provide:

* A clean medication tracking dashboard
* Secure patient information handling
* Medication administration recording
* Time-based medication filtering
* Monthly schedule visualization
* Reliable data storage and updates
